But the court yesterday made a premises closure order and said the family should be immediately evicted.

They were given until 4pm to remove their personal belongings before the property was boarded up.

One neighbour, who did not want to be named, said: 'They were the original neighbours from hell.

'They never gave a thought to anyone else living here - they were trouble from start to finish.

'People's lives have been ruined by their awful behaviour - it has been total misery.

